Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index is a stock index of The Stock Exchange of Hong Kong for red chip. Red chip were the companies listed on the exchange, incorporated outside mainland China (Bermuda, the Cayman Islands or Hong Kong), but majority owned by the central or regional government of the People's Republic of China.
As of February 2015, there are 25 red chips that compose this index.
In the past, the constituents of Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index did not intersect with H shares' Hang Seng China Enterprises Index, as H share and red chip companies did not intersect. But a possible inclusion of the top red chip companies to Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index in 2018, was announced in August 2017.
Some of the constituents of Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index was also the constituents of Hang Seng Index (the blue-chip index). They were known as purple-chip in the past.
